Creating a modern and efficient website using **React** with **Server-Side Rendering (SSR)** involves a structured approach that combines React's component-based architecture with SSR for enhanced performance and user experience. Below is a detailed breakdown of the implementation:

---

### **1. Project Setup**
- **Initialize the React App**:  
  ```bash
  npx create-react-app modern-website-ssr
  cd modern-website-ssr
  ```

- **Install Dependencies**:  
  ```bash
  npm install express react-router-dom
  ```

---

### **2. Server-Side Rendering (SSR) Implementation**
- **Create a Server (Express)**:  
  Create a `server.js` file to handle HTTP requests and serve React pages.  
  ```javascript
  const express = require('express');
  const app = express();
  const path = require('path');
  const React = require('react');
  const ReactDOMServer = require('react-dom/server');
  const { renderToString } = require('react-dom/server');

  app.get('*', (req, res) => {
    const html = ReactDOMServer.renderToString(
      <React.StrictMode>
        <App />
      </React.StrictMode>
    );

    res.send(`
      <!DOCTYPE html>
      <html>
        <head>
          <title>Modern Website</title>
          <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
        </head>
        <body>
          <div id="root">${html}</div>
          <script src="/bundle.js"></script>
        </body>
      </html>
    `);
  });

  app.listen(3000, () => {
    console.log('Server running on http://localhost:3000');
  });
  ```

---

### **3. React App Structure**
- **Folder Structure**:
  ```
  modern-website-ssr/
  ├── public/
  │   ├── index.html
  │   ├── styles.css
  │   └── bundle.js
  ├── src/
  │   ├── App.js
  │   ├── components/
  │   │   ├── Header.js
  │   │   ├── Hero.js
  │   │   ├── About.js
  │   │   └── Footer.js
  │   ├── routes/
