### Perl Script: Haversine Distance Calculation

This script calculates the distance between two points on the Earth's surface using the Haversine formula. It handles input validation, error cases, and provides results in both kilometers and miles. The script is well-documented and includes test cases.

```perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use JSON;
use LWP::Simple;
use HTTP::Request;

# Haversine formula
sub haversine_distance {
    my ($lat1, $lon1, $lat2, $lon2) = @_;
    my $R = 6371; # Earth radius in kilometers

    my $lat1_rad = $lat1 * pi / 180;
    my $lon1_rad = $lon1 * pi / 180;
    my $lat2_rad = $lat2 * pi / 180;
    my $lon2_rad = $lon2 * pi / 180;

    my $dlat = $lat2_rad - $lat1_rad;
    my $dlon = $lon2_rad - $lon1_rad;

    my $a = (sin($dlat / 2) ** 2) + cos($lat1_rad) * cos($lat2_rad) * (sin($dlon / 2) ** 2);
    my $c = 2 * atan2(sqrt($a), sqrt(1 - $a));
    my $distance = $R * $c;

    return $distance;
}

